metadata.name: The Unequal Marriage
metadata.description: The young lover of mysterious and wealthy Parisian Madeleine Bark has long been in the position of a dowry boy. The image of an innocent bride screams about his readiness for an unequal marriage. He does it for the sake of the opportunity to make an invaluable gift for International Women's Day. He will give away his unlimited right to ARBEITEN, and begin to relax in the sweat of his face [de. entspannen] for the women of the world while drinking cold German beer.
